node.text:
thank you @chrisandrews2017 

Almost 3 and a half years ago it was recommended by a jury at an inquest that the establishment of a National Governing Body (NGB) for MMA should be expedited. This would, among other things, give our association the regulatory powers to ensure all promotions use the highest safety standards currently recommended by IMMAA which acts as our nation's de facto NGB. Safety standards for Irish MMA now surpass all other contact sports in Ireland, in fact probably worldwide. As well as this we provide coaching courses, child protection courses, officials training, national squad training and all the other normal workings of a NGB. 
To date we have received nothing but roadblocks from the Irish Martial Arts Commission (IMAC) who act as the umbrella NGB for martial arts in Ireland. We are, again, asking for help from Sport Ireland to finalise our application for NGB status so we can get back to the job of providing safe training environments to our 1000s of members countrywide who look forward to representing their country with pride on the international stage thru IMMAF amatuer competition. node.text:
As the world begins to re-open and W2W seasons start again worldwide this is a fun look back at Sydney’s finale before the world was hit so hard. Its heartening to know their next finale is only weeks away!  W2W @citykickboxing have nearly ONE HUNDRED men and women starting their MMA journey just this week alone. Myself and the knowledgeable @coachowenroddy have more than 450 applications for our upcoming Battle of Dublin. Over the coming months there will be seasons starting in most parts of the world. If you are the owner of an exceptional Combat Sports Academy and can handle 30 or 40 new students the day you re-open then get in touch NOW! Go to my bio for more or email info@wimp2warrior.com to set up a call.
@wimp2warrior - changing lives thru Martial Arts.

node.text:
It's been a pleasure and honour to coach @rushammer for the past decade and I wish him the very best in the future. As a novice 1-1 pro he insisted on fighting one of UKs hottest prospect, the 9-1 Dave Hill. He won and that attitude of anyone, anytime, any rules would define his +10yr professional fighter. Win or lose he showed up, made weight and always gave it his all. 
I'm looking forward to seeing what he does next ❤
